  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to compare the results of skin testing and ELISPOT assay in patients with a
      history of non-immediate reactions to cephalosporins
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with a history of non-immediate reactions to cephalosporins will be tested by patch
      test and/or intradermal test. Peripheral blood mononuclear cells will be collected to
      analyzed cytokine secretions by ELISPOT assay
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
